                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d969">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/1742.</note>
                <head>[Telegrams—Paraphrase.]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 18, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Exiled Zelayistas in Costa Rica headed by Irias and supplemented by Estrada
                    Cabrera are about to move against Nicaragua. Seven machine guns for them are
                    coming from New Orleans. The foregoing is reported by the Nicaraguan chargé
                    d’affaires in Costa Rica.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
